Notes
=====

* 2.6.14 will provide /dev/bus/usb/ devices which can be managed with udev. Get rid of usbfs
  $ tree /sys/class/usb_device/
  The presence of the "dev" file lets udev create real device nodes: tree /dev/bus/usb/
  udev rule:
    SUBSYSTEM="usb_device", PROGRAM="/sbin/usb_device %k", NAME="%c"
    (echo $1 | /bin/sed 's/usb\([0-9]*\)\.\([0-9]*\)/bus\/usb\/\1\/\2/')
  This makes libusb pick up the real nodes instead of the mounted usbfs:
    export USB_DEVFS_PATH=/dev/bus/usb
  -- ftp://ftp.tugraz.at/mirror/kernel/kernel/v2.6/ChangeLog-2.6.14
* kernel versions 2.6.14 and later are providing *old* ieee80211
  and ipw2200 1.0 drivers as part of the mainline tree. -> exclude/disable ieee80211 and ipw2200
  -- http://ipw2200.sourceforge.net/INSTALL
* I've already received three different serious bug reports about problems with netfilter/iptables in 2.6.14.
  -- http://gnumonks.org/~laforge/weblog/2005/11/01#20051101-bugs

